		<img src="/bullying/getinvolved/images/unityawardbios/rachel-bio.jpg" width="175" height="250" alt=""/>
		<p><strong>Why is bullying prevention important to you? </strong>It is important to give a voice to the ones who are fearful of who will judge and bully them. There needs to be an end to bullying and I know we can help to conquer this goal.</p>
		<p><strong>Two things you want people to know about you: </strong>My mom has been a longtime volunteer at PACER and now is a worker at PACER, head of PACER benefit silent auction. I am traveling around Asia this summer for 5 weeks.</p>
		<p><strong>Advice to prevent bullying: </strong>Don’t be afraid to stand up and show your appreciation for kids being bullied. It’s completely unacceptable for kids to be bullied for who they are and no one to make a stand. It is amazing to be able to be commemorated for your actions of standing up.</p>
